14	// Directed Verification Testbench for `axi_lite_mailbox`.
15	// - On port 0 all registers get read and the expected results asserted.
16	// - Read from an empty read FIFO on Port 0 and clear its interrupt
17	// - Request some data from the other port.
18	//    - Port 0 sends one data_t to the other and sets its read threshold and waits until
19	//      port 1 fills the FIFO to a certain value. Port one waits for its interrupt, sets a
20	//      write threshold and fills the FIFO, until it reaches it. While the FIFO is filling,
21	//      port 0 starts emptying the read FIFO, however is slower than port 1 pushing, as port
22	//      0 checks if the FIFO is empty. Port 1 stops sending, when the interrupt for its write
23	//      threshold is recieved. Port 0 empties the FIFO completely and resets its read interrupt.
24	// - Port 0 flushes both FIFOs
25	// - Port 0 enables error interrupt and pushes data until the FIFO errors, then clears it by
26	//   flushing the FIFOs and reading the `ERROR` register.
27	// - Port 0 makes an unmapped read and write access, and some targeted accesses to get the branch
28	//   coverage to 96.25%, the not taken branches have to do with the stalling
29	//   capabilities of the slave, when the response path is not ready.
30	// Each of these tests has the respective AXI Lite transaction asserted in the expected output.
31	// Simulation end tells the number of failed assertions.
32	
33	`include "axi/typedef.svh"
34	`include "axi/assign.svh"
